OL,5, Faye Johnson-Smith thought it was too  
OL,6, good to be true when her boss said she 
OL,7, could have every Wednesday off without 
OL,8, a cut in her pay.                      
OL,10,FHer employer was taking part in a      
OL,11,Fsix-month trial, testing the costs and 
OL,12,Fbenefits of a four-day week.           
OL,14,FLike most of the workers involved, Faye
OL,15,Ffound she was healthier and happier as 
OL,16,Fa result of working shorter hours.     
OL,18,FBut at the end of the trial almost all 
OL,19,Fthe 61 employers involved were also    
OL,20,Fkeen to keep the new work pattern.     
